  "prompt": "Which API does ResearchGate use to get the list of institutions?",
  "response": "ResearchGate uses the \"ResearchGate Institutions API\" to retrieve the list of institutions. This API allows developers to access a comprehensive database of academic and research institutions from around the world. To use this API, you would need to make a GET request to the endpoint: `https://www.researchgate.net/institutions`. \n\nHere is an example of how you can use the API in Python:\n\n```python\nimport requests\n\n# Make a GET request to the ResearchGate Institutions API\nresponse = requests.get('https://www.researchgate.net/institutions')\n\n# Check if the request was successful\nif response.status_code == 200:\n    # Parse the JSON response\n    institutions = response.json()\n    \n    # Print the list of institutions\n    for institution in institutions:\n        print(institution['name'])\nelse:\n    print('Failed to retrieve institutions. Status code:', response.status_code)\n```\n\nPlease note that you may need an API key or authentication token to access this API, depending on ResearchGate's current policies. Always review and adhere to the API's terms of use and any applicable rate limits when making requests.",
